th","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 22, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNone of you should wish for death due to a calamity that has afflicted him. Yet if he must do something, let him say: O Allah, keep me alive so long as life is good for me,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2935,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/18\/death-only-his-deeds-remain\/","url_meta":{"origin":17374,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Death: After death, only his deeds remain","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThree things follow a deceased person. Two of them return and one remains. His family, his wealth, and his deeds follow him. His family and wealth return, but his deeds remain.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6149,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36269,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/21\/islam-plus-hasanat\/","url_meta":{"origin":17374,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Tawbah: Embracing Islam plus good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 21, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Tawil reported: He came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cWhat do you